<!-- 11 ROAS -->
<div class="sec" id="roas">11 · ROAS & Profitability</div>

<div class="card">
  <div class="card-title">ROAS — Return on Ad Spend</div>
  <div class="card-sub">How much revenue you earn for every $1 spent on ads</div>
  <div class="card-desc">Formula: Revenue from Ads ÷ Ad Spend = ROAS. A ROAS of 3 means for every $1 spent, you earned $3 back. Most important metric for sales campaigns.</div>
  <table>
    <tr><th>ROAS</th><th>Remark</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Below 1x</td><td><span class="pill po">Losing money — pause immediately</span></td></tr>
    <tr><td>1x – 2x</td><td><span class="pill po">Breaking even or slight loss — fix urgently</span></td></tr>
    <tr><td>2x – 3x</td><td><span class="pill av">Average — profitable but thin margin</span></td></tr>
    <tr><td>3x – 5x</td><td><span class="pill g">Good — healthy profitability</span></td></tr>
    <tr><td>5x – 8x</td><td><span class="pill vg">Very Good — scale this campaign</span></td></tr>
    <tr><td>8x+</td><td><span class="pill ex">Excellent — scale aggressively</span></td></tr>
  </table>
  <div class="tip"><strong>Break-even ROAS formula:</strong> 1 ÷ Your Profit Margin = Break Even ROAS. Example: if your margin is 40%, break even ROAS = 1 ÷ 0.4 = 2.5x. You need above 2.5x to be profitable.</div>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <div class="card-title">CPA — Cost Per Acquisition</div>
  <div class="card-sub">How much you spend to get one paying customer</div>
  <div class="card-desc">Formula: Total Ad Spend ÷ Number of Purchases. Must be lower than your product profit to be sustainable.</div>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Rule</th><th>Detail</th></tr>
    <tr><td>CPA must be</td><td>Lower than your profit per order</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Example</td><td>Product sells for $20, costs $8 to make = $12 profit. CPA must be below $12.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Healthy CPA</td><td><span class="pill g">Below 30% of product selling price</span></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Dangerous CPA</td><td><span class="pill po">Above 60% of product selling price</span></td></tr>
  </table>
</div>

<!-- 12 HEALTH CHECK -->
<div class="sec" id="health">12 · Campaign Health Check</div>

<div class="card">
  <div class="card-title">Quick Health Check — Ask These Every Week</div>
  <div class="card-sub">Run through this checklist every time you review your ads</div>
  <ul class="checklist">
    <li>Is Frequency below 3.5? If above — refresh creative immediately</li>
    <li>Is CTR above 1%? If below — change image or first line of copy</li>
    <li>Are Quality Rankings all Average or Above Average? If below — fix ad creative</li>
    <li>Is Landing Page Views at least 60% of Link Clicks? If below — fix website speed</li>
    <li>Is CPM rising week over week? If yes — audience getting saturated, expand or refresh</li>
    <li>Has the campaign had at least 7 days to learn? If no — don't judge results yet</li>
    <li>Is ROAS above break-even? If no — pause and fix before spending more</li>
    <li>Are messages and leads being followed up within 5 minutes? If no — fix your response process</li>
    <li>Is budget at least the minimum for the objective? If no — increase or change objective</li>
    <li>Are you retargeting website visitors and cart abandoners? If no — set this up this week</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <div class="card-title">When to Pause vs When to Fix vs When to Scale</div>
  <div class="card-sub">Decision framework for every campaign situation</div>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Situation</th><th>Action</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Good CTR, 0 conversions, above average rankings</td><td><span class="pill av">Fix website — not the ad</span></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Low CTR (below 0.8%), poor rankings</td><td><span class="pill po">Fix or replace the ad creative</span></td></tr>
    <tr><td>High CPM, small audience</td><td><span class="pill av">Expand audience or refresh creative</span></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Frequency above 4.0</td><td><span class="pill po">Add new creative immediately</span></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Good ROAS (3x+) for 7+ days</td><td><span class="pill g">Scale — increase budget by 20%</span></td></tr>
